The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Bharti AXA kickstarts operations

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Mittal: New avenues

 Hyderabad, Aug. 22: Bharti AXA Life Insurance Company Ltd has kicked off its operations in Hyderabad and plans to open 30 more branches across the country by December 2007.

 The joint venture between French insurance firm AXA and Bharti Enterprises has lined up an aggressive strategy to capture a major share of the domestic life insurance market, CEO Nitin Chopra said.

 It plans to invest Rs 500 crore in three years to promote its business model, which includes a foray into pension and mutual fund sectors as and when regulations permit.

 The company has selected Hyderabad for its first branch because of the vibrant metropolitan culture truly representative of the upbeat urbanism in the country.

 The Company has introduced two unit-linked products Future Confident and Wealth Confident.

 Chopra said the insurance sector had the potential to grow at 40 per cent.

 The Bharti AXA combine will leverage Bharti Airtels distribution capabilities, its customer base of over 25 million and its telecom retail experience, while AXA will bring its global insurance expertise and asset management skills to the partnership. The joint venture will also use AXAs business processing set-up, AXA Business Services, to offer services.

 Mark Pearson, regional chief executive of AXA Asia Pacific Holdings Ltd, said the AXA academy would provide in-house training in management practices to suit the Indian market. Opening of the first branch signifies the French firms strong commitment to the Indian insurance market, he added.

 Sunil Bharti Mittal, chairman and group managing director of Bharti Enterprises, and chairman of Bharti AXA Life Insurance, said, The launch of the first branch of Bharti AXA Life Insurance is a major step towards accomplishing Bhartis vision to play a dominant role in the financial services sector. 




